  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>You may need to adjust the price of an item or service after the customer has already made a payment based on the original price, even though the ticket remains open. This could involve applying a price override or a discount to reflect the updated pricing. This article will walk you through the process of adjusting the item\u2019s price and issuing a partial refund to the customer</p><h3 id=\"Refunds:IssueaPartialRefundforaPriceOverrideorDiscountonanOpenTicket-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933279378/Virtual+Cash+Terminal+VCT+Refund+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933279378\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) Refund Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933639827\" rel=\"nofollow\">Assign a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) to Accept Payments</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154652.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Refunds:IssueaPartialRefundforaPriceOverrideorDiscountonanOpenTicket-IssueaPriceAdjustmentandPartialRefund\">Issue a Price Adjustment and Partial Refund</h2><p>A VCT must be assigned to the terminal to perform a refund on a ticket.</p><p /><p>Search for the open ticket in your Ticket Queue. On the Ticket View page, click the <strong>Edit Button</strong> along the row of actions on the upper-right section of the page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154702.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154705.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"Refunds:IssueaPartialRefundforaPriceOverrideorDiscountonanOpenTicket-AdjustPricingfortheLineItem\">Adjust Pricing for the Line Item</h3><p>In the Ticket Items section, enter the necessary price change or discount for the item(s). The Ticket Totals section will now show a pending refund amount.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154708.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"211\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154711.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"Refunds:IssueaPartialRefundforaPriceOverrideorDiscountonanOpenTicket-RefundaPartialAmount\">Refund a Partial Amount </h3><p>On the Transaction section of the ticket, click the <strong>Refund Button </strong>under the Actions column.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Alternatively, you can click <strong>Add Transaction</strong>\u00a0on the left side of the Transactions section.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154714.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>An Add Transaction pop-up will appear. Select the refund payment type and enter the refund amount as a positive value. Make sure the <strong>Refund In Full checkbox is unchecked</strong>. Once you have entered the information and additional notes, click <strong>Submit Refund</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note:\u00a0</strong>A refund can be performed for Integrated Payments without the card being present, however, there is a limit of one refund per Bluefin card transaction.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154718.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Verify the transaction as posted to the ticket and that the payment has been issued to the customer. Once the <strong>balance due is $0.00</strong>, you can <strong>Save\u00a0</strong>or\u00a0<strong>Close </strong>the ticket to finalize the process.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672585/image-20230627-154721.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.22.X</p>",
